            The proposed investment is to Discovery World Corporation (the Company), a company established in 1993, and listed in the Philippine Stock Exchange in 2013. The Company is primarily engaged in development and operations of hotel and resorts in the Philippines. It has several operating assets: 


         (i)  

             

         Discovery Shores Boracay  established in 2007, is a resort hotel located in Boat Station 1 of the island of Boracay, Aklan. Having 86 hotel rooms, and 11 villas currently under construction, this is currently DWCs largest property.    


         (ii)  

             

         Club Paradise (owned by DWC subsidiary, Euro-Pacific Resorts, Inc.) Located in Coron, Palawan, this resort has 56 guest rooms and is currently being refurbished.    


         (iii)  

             

         The Discovery Fleet (owned by DWC subsidiary, Discovery Fleet Corp.)  composed of vessels for scuba safari expeditions such as in Tubbataha Reef, Coron (Palawan) and Apo Reef (Eastern Visayas).       


         The Project involves the construction and development of two new hotel projects in two different sites, a 117 room hotel and 84-bed hostel, with commercial area and beach club in El Nido, Palawan and a hotel and commercial development in La Trinidad, Benguet with at least 127 rooms.  The proceeds of the IFC investment will finance the construction, fit out and other costs related to the construction of these two hotel projects.

