           The Project involves two sites: 


         1. 

             

         Vanilla Beach Project  located in Sitio Marimegmeg, Barangay Corong. El Nido, Palawan.  The property is a vacant land, in a rural area located within the El Nido-Taytay Managed Resource Protected Area, the largest marine sanctuary in the Philippines. It is about 2.5 kms from the El Nido town proper and is accessible via the Palawan North Road, typically through public transportation (buses and shuttle vans from Puerto Princesa, Palawans capital), and tricycles for shorter distances, as well as private vehicles. The nearest airport is the Lio Airport in El Nido which is 4 km away and can be accessed via boat or road travel. As Lio airport currently handles small 50-seater aircraft, the site can also be accessed through the Puerto Princesa airport though about 230 km distance, travel is in general through paved national and provincial roads.  


         2. 

             

         Discovery Mountain Resort Project  located in Beckel Road, Barangay Beckel, La Trinidad, Benguet. La Trinidad is the capital city of the Province of Benguet, it is considered a rural area with agriculture being the municipalitys main economic activity. The site is traversed by the Shilan-Beckel access road connecting to the main Ambuklao Road, which is the access road to Baguio City and Nueva Vizcaya. Modes of transportation are public utility jeepneys and shuttle vans. It is about 250 km away from Manila and visitors to the La Trinidad-Baguio area typically reach the area through an approximately 4-5 hour land travel via private vehicle.
